19 Section 1 of this bill establishes a procedure for obtaining a court order to
20 authorize the involuntary administration of psychiatric medication to a defendant
21 committed to the custody of the Division. Section 1 also requires the court to make
22 specific findings before issuing such an order. Under existing law, a court is
23 authorized to include the involuntary administration of medication in an order
24 committing a defendant to the custody of the Division. (NRS 178.425) Section 3 of
25 this bill removes this authorization and instead requires the prosecuting attorney to
26 seek a separate court order for the involuntary administration of psychiatric
27 medication using the procedure established in section 1. Section 2 of this bill
28 makes certain definitions in existing law relating to the competency of a defendant
29 applicable to section 1.
